## Questions?

**Q: Can I make money using this?**  
A: Yes. You can build and sell products that use >the_collective.

**Q: Can I modify the code?**  
A: Yes. You can fork, modify, and customize it per Apache 2.0 and MPL 2.0 terms.

**Q: Can I sell ">the_collective" itself?**  
A: No. You cannot resell >the_collective framework as a standalone product. You can only sell products/services built WITH it.

**Q: Can I rebrand the agent personas?**  
A: No. The agent names and their specific character configurations are trademarked and cannot be claimed as original work. You can create your own custom agents with those names, but not as a derived work of >the_collective unless you provide proper attribution.

**Q: Do I need to attribute >the_collective?**  
A: Yes. Attribution is a license requirement and just a kind of "good neighbor" practice.

**Q: Can I use this commercially without attribution?**  
A: No. Both the Apache 2.0 and MPL 2.0 licenses require attribution and copyright notice retention depending on your implementation.

